MISSING: &nbsp;Merit Nyakbuba (10).&nbsp;Photo: Makhado SAPS.Date: 26 December 2016 By: Isabel VenterViewed: 5238The Makhado Police have asked the public to be on the lookout for a missing 10-year-old girl.According to local police spokesperson, Const Irene Radzilane, Merit Nyakbuba was kidnapped from her family home in 66 Kruger Street, in Louis Trichardt,&nbsp;earlier this morning (24 December).&ldquo;It is alleged that an unknown male came to the residence under the pretence that he needs accommodation. After his departure the mother notice that her child was missing,&rdquo; said Radzilane.The man allegedly told the girl that he will go buy her sweets. He was wearing trousers and a black shirt with grey stripes.Anyone with information on the girl&rsquo;s whereabouts is urged to contact the Makhado Police station at Tel 015&nbsp;519 4300 or Const Radzilane at 082 565 8233.&nbsp;UPDATE:&nbsp;The Makhado Police have confirmed that the 10-year-old Merit Nyakbuba have been found and returned to her family.According to the police she was found yesterday, 25 December, near the Mopani area (Musina) in the company of 40-year-old Zimbabwean man. The police have managed to arrest the man.&ldquo;The girl managed to slip away for her alleged abductor around 14:00, and alerted members of the community,&rdquo; said the provincial police spokesperson Brig. Motlafela Mojapelo.&ldquo;The motive for the incident is not know at this stage, but all possibilities are being investigated,&rdquo; Mojapelo added.According to him Merit was taken to hospital, and then released in her family&rsquo;s care. The investigation is on-going and more details will be released as they become available.Isabel joined the Zoutpansberger and Limpopo Mirror in 2009 as a reporter. She holds a BA Degree in Communication Sciences from the University of South Africa. Her beat is mainly crime and court reporting.Email: isabel@zoutnet.co.zaMore photos... 